{
  "stem": "3952.5",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But people recognized them or found out that they are not one of ours, so they had to question them.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So I was there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then, after-- after Admont, we went to Italy.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "In 31st-- the night of 31st of December, 1945, we-- my brother, one brother of mine, and myself and my sister-- one of my sisters-- the three of us crossed the border, the Brenners.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Now, the Brenners if you know-- now I know very well-- that if I want to go to Genoa, in Switzerland, from Milano, I have to take the car, put the car on the train, and cross the Brenner Mountains in the tunnel, with the train, because the Brenners, even in May, June, is covered with snow.",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We walked on the 31st of December, 1945.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We crossed the border into Italy, from Austria into Italy.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Probably the border guards were paid off by the-- by the Israeli troops, by the Haganah that they-- we were crossing, like, a few hundred meters behind them.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Or maybe they didn't hear it in the snow.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we were there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We came to a certain-- to a certain man who had a shack and kept us in that shack.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We were 101 persons.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "He kept us in a shack for-- it was a Saturday night and the whole of Sunday.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Was-- that was New Year's, the 1st of January.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "The whole of Sunday we were in that shack.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And I thought that after Auschwitz, Wolfsberg, Ebensee, here is where I'm going to die.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "I'm going to freeze to death.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "This is unbelievable, the cold it was.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Up in the mountains on the Brenner, it was so bitter cold, you can't imagine.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
